---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Operational Data Systems"
  description="Automation, reporting pipelines, dashboards, and MIS systems for UK SMEs. Eliminate manual work and give your team real-time visibility. Typical timeline: 2-4 weeks."
>
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <span class="text-sm font-medium text-brand-blue bg-brand-blue-pale px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Typical timeline: 2–4 weeks</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate">Operational Data Systems</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-xl text-slate-light">
        Automation pipelines, live dashboards, and data integration that eliminate manual work and give your team real-time visibility. Stop copying data between systems—we build automation that handles the repetitive work.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 prose prose-lg max-w-none text-slate-light">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate">The Problem</h2>
        <p>
          Your team spends hours every week on tasks that feel like they should be automatic:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Pulling data from one system and reformatting it for another</li>
          <li>Creating the same weekly report from scratch</li>
          <li>Reconciling spreadsheets that never quite match</li>
          <li>Chasing updates that should arrive automatically</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Every hour spent on manual data work is an hour not spent on decisions, customers, or strategy.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate mt-12">What We Build</h2>
        <div class="not-prose grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate">Automated Reporting</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-light text-sm">Reports that build themselves—pulling from multiple sources, applying your logic, delivered on schedule.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate">Data Pipeline Automation</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-light text-sm">Connect your systems so data flows automatically—no more copy-paste between tools.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate">Alert Systems</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-light text-sm">Get notified when something needs attention—before it becomes a problem.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate">Workflow Automation</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-light text-sm">Automate repetitive processes end-to-end, with human review where needed.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate mt-12">Typical Results</h2>
        <p>
          Based on our project patterns, automation typically delivers:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>10-15 hours saved per week</strong> on reporting tasks</li>
          <li><strong>Elimination of manual errors</strong> in data transfer</li>
          <li><strong>Same-day visibility</strong> instead of weekly lag</li>
          <li><strong>Scalable processes</strong> that don't require more headcount</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-sm italic">Results vary by scope and data quality. We agree success metrics upfront.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate mt-12">How It Works</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Discovery (30 min):</strong> We identify your highest-impact automation opportunities</li>
          <li><strong>Assessment (1-3 days):</strong> We map your current workflow and design the automated version</li>
          <li><strong>Build (2-4 weeks):</strong> We build, test, and deploy the automation</li>
          <li><strong>Handover:</strong> Full documentation, training, and optional ongoing support</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    title="Ready to automate?"
    description="Book a discovery call to identify your highest-ROI automation opportunities."
  />
</BaseLayout>
